StepBegin(n=20)
ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I understand the pattern. The project uses Kratos which has defau
lt gRPC error handling. `exception.Exception` implements `error` interface, and 
when returned from service layer, Kratos\'s gRPC encoder should handle it. But f
or specific gRPC codes like `codes.InvalidArgument` and `codes.PermissionDenied`
, the service layer should convert them.\n\nLooking at the layers.md example:\n`
``go\n// Biz → Service：转换为 gRPC 错误码\nfunc (s *UserService) GetUser(ctx co
ntext.Context, req *pb.GetUserRequest) (*pb.GetUserResponse, error) {\n    user,
err := s.uc.GetUser(ctx, req.Id)\n    if err != nil {\n        if errors.Is(err,
repo.ErrNotFound) {\n            return nil, status.Error(codes.NotFound, err.Er
ror())\n        }\n        return nil, status.Error(codes.Internal, err.Error())
\n    }\n    return &pb.GetUserResponse{User: convert(user)}, nil\n}\n```\n\nSo 
the service layer should convert biz errors to gRPC errors. The current IM servi
ce just passes errors through:\n```go\nfunc (s *IMService) SendMessage(ctx conte
xt.Context, req *apipb.SendMessageRequest) (*apipb.SendMessageResponse, error) {
\n    uid, err := meta.TryLoadUid(ctx)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil,
err\n    }\n    msg, err := s.imUC.SendMessage(ctx, uid, req)\n    if err != nil
{\n        return nil, err  // passes through without conversion\n    }\n    ret
urn &apipb.SendMessageResponse{Message: msg}, nil\n}\n```\n\nThe review says:\n1
. Remove `google.golang.org/grpc/codes` and `google.golang.org/grpc/status` from
biz layer\n2. Define biz layer domain errors like `var ErrInvalidArgument = exce
ption.New(400, "invalid argument", "参数错误")`\n3. Return these domain errors f
rom biz layer\n4. In service layer, convert domain errors to gRPC `status.Error`
\n\nLet me check if there\'s an existing pattern for converting exception to gRP
C status in other services.',
    encrypted=None
)
