ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think="I see there's no custom gRPC error encoder. Let me check how Kratos h
andles `exception.Exception` in gRPC transport. Kratos by default uses its own e
rror type (`errors.New`) which gets encoded to gRPC status. But `exception.Excep
tion` is a custom type that implements `error`.\n\nLooking at the review more ca
refully:\n> 4. 在 `internal/service/wapi/im.go` 中将领域错误转换为 gRPC `status.
Error`（参考 `layers.md` 第 10.2 节示例）\n\nSo I DO need to convert in the serv
ice layer. Let me also check if there's a standard way to do this conversion. Th
e simplest approach is to check for specific biz errors in the service layer and
convert them to `status.Error`.\n\nLet me also check how the existing biz layer 
tests work for im.go.",
    encrypted=None
)
